n't that be nifty.<br><br>Ofcourse, we would need to build big telescopes in order to find such a target and aim. It would be a hell of a challenge. Years would elapse between firing and striking it. During that time celestial movements would come into play ofcourse. Theoretically possible though I think. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=cattlecar>cattlecar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>NERVA Spaceplane Pilot</span><br>  Posts: 232<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(7/12/02 9:00:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.earthlink.net/~macami/ez/spinthingie.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/images/posticons/spaceh.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: How to create a death star style laser in theory.</span><hr size=1> PO, you have stumbled onto the secret that the governments of the world have been hiding<br>for years now.  Green house gases aren't responsible for the global warming.<br>The Earth is under attack from the star system 55 Cancri.  These insidious aliens<br>have pointed their massive death laser at our planet.  Fortunately for us, it disperses<br>quite a bit by the time it gets here!  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm20.showPrevMessage?topicID=27.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm20.showNextMessage?topicID=27.topic"> Next Top